properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued February 12 at 10:35AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Grand Forks ND
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Warning, dangerously cold wind chills.
Wind chills as low as 45 below zero. For the Blizzard Warning,
blizzard conditions. No additional snow accumulations expected.
Winds gusting as high as 50 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of west central Minnesota and southeast North
Dakota.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Warning, until noon CST Thursday.
For the Blizzard Warning, until 4 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. Gusty
winds could bring down tree branches. The dangerously cold
wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little
as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

Travel should be restricted to emergencies only. If you must
travel, have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded,
stay with your vehicle.

The latest road conditions for North Dakota can be found at
dot.nd.gov/travel and for Minnesota at 511mn.org, or by calling
5 1 1 in either state.
